{
  "name": "Horn of Blasting",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>You can use an action to speak the horn's command word and then blow the horn, which emits a thunderous blast in a 30-foot &amp;Reference[cone]{cone} that is audible 600 feet away. Each creature in the &amp;Reference[cone]{cone} must make a [[/save con 15 format=long]]. On a failed save, a creature takes 5d6 &amp;Reference[thunder]{thunder} damage and is &amp;Reference[deafened]{deafened} for 1 minute. On a successful save, a creature takes half as much damage and isn't &amp;Reference[deafened]{deafened}. Creatures and objects made of glass or crystal have disadvantage on the saving throw and take 10d6 &amp;Reference[thunder]{thunder} damage instead of 5d6.</p>\n<p>Each use of the horn's magic has a 20 percent chance of causing the horn to explode. The explosion deals 10d6 &amp;Reference[fire]{fire} damage to the blower and destroys the horn.</p>\n</div>",
